full_text:
I used to be really afraid of making calls and then I moved out on my own and I have to get/make them all the time, and I rarely get nervous.

The receptionist or customer service people are there to help you, and they make tons of calls a day! They are usually very gracious.
full_text(utf-8): b'I used to be really afraid of making calls and then I moved out on my own and I have to get/make them all the time, and I rarely get nervous.\n\nThe receptionist or customer service people are there to help you, and they make tons of calls a day! They are usually very gracious.'

full_text:
- It‚Äôs perfectly okay if they ask you to repeat yourself or if you need them to repeat something that was said. You guys have the same goal! Sometimes you need clarity üòä

- Making a flub or misspeaking is no biggie! Just correct yourself and keep going!

Sometimes you need clarity \xf0\x9f\x98\x8a\n\n- Making a flub or misspeaking is no biggie! Just correct yourself and keep going!'

full_text: - If you‚Äôre ordering food, they want your business! Restaurants are usually great on the phone and can decipher the oddest of calls. And food orders are great practice! If you like a place and order often, you‚Äôll get to develop the skill with low stakes!

full_text: - If you are dreading a call, make it as early as you can, like when the place opens. If it‚Äôs for something like the bank or an appointment, the line will probably be clear and you won‚Äôt have to wait on hold as long.

full_text:
